comments: Dinwiddie (DAL) makes contact with the ball as simultaneous arm contact occurs with Porter Jr. (HOU), which is marginal.
Green (HOU) and Bullock (DAL) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Bullock (DAL) is already in Smith Jr.'s (HOU) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Wood (DAL) is moving alongside Gordon's (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Wood (DAL) cleanly blocks the shot attempt before it touches the backboard.
Martin Jr. (HOU) legally contests Wood's (DAL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Wood (DAL) and Martin Jr. (HOU) come together at the same spot as they pursue the loose ball.  Wood then cleanly ties up Martin Jr. and a jump ball is correctly called.
Porter Jr. (HOU) briefly grasps Doncic's (DAL) jersey and marginal contact occurs as Doncic secures possession.
Wood (DAL) is firming up in Porter Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver contact during the pick.
Martin Jr. (HOU) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Porter Jr.'s (HOU) momentum carries him towards Wood (DAL) and marginal contact occurs off ball.
Martin Jr. (HOU) and Doncic (DAL) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Dinwiddie (DAL) is bracing for the contact from Smith Jr. (HOU) and marginal contact occurs as Dinwiddie releases away from the contact.
Dinwiddie (DAL) reaches across Sengun's (HOU) body and initiates contact with his side during his drive toward the rim.
Gordon (HOU) cleanly deflects the ball away from Doncic (DAL).
Gordon (HOU) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Smith Jr. (HOU) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
Doncic (DAL) and Martin Jr. (HOU) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Porter Jr. (HOU) jumps slightly forward towards Doncic (DAL) and marginal contact occurs as Doncic receives the pass.
Green (HOU) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
Sengun (HOU) and Wood (DAL) briefly engage and disengage as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
